column5: Sorry John, but comparing Illinois sweet corn to Canadian sweet corn is like comparing Illinois Walleye fishing to Canadian Walleye fishing LOL How about we bring up some corn and you provide the walleyes and we will have a fish fry in the middle of the bridge over the rainy river in Fort Frances. LOL
Won't be long you'll be going over the bridge,you can catch your own fish.
Might as well ! Nobody's using it !
Won't be to long now john and the Ontario 500 is going to be held on the 502.
It's look nice, I'm jealous Sent from my iPhone using Tapatalk

What goes best with walleye? Sweet corn is right up there, but to me the ultimate combination is fresh tomatoes. Add a few first-cut ears of corn and now you've got a feast. My cardiologist, if I had one, might object to the salt intake, but it'd be worth it. I think I'll wash it down with a Molson!
Yeah. and throw in some "junk potatoes" and fixed up baked beans and you have the ultimate northwoods feast.
Oh yeah we call them Doctored beans but I know what you mean! you cant beat them
SWEETCORN! Pooch PS: Eat your heart out Skywagon!!
Looks very good,but I want at those eyes.
Try to keep this quite but we have some oretty delicious corn in Canada to.
Quote: Originally Posted by prov1800Try to keep this quite but we have some oretty delicious corn in Canada to.We're locked out john we can't even get to your corn fields.

That is just cruel! and nobody to bring me any across the border. Our sweet corn will not be ready until the end of August/first of September. Just to reciprocate.... here is a picture of a 27" that a friend caught when we were at the cabin last week.
Very nice,sweet corn n walleye dinner doesn't get any better than that.

Guess we're even. That's a nice fishy. Right now I'd trade a burlap bag of sweet corn for one of those in a heartbeat!Good looking garden. I'm always amazed at the progression of the maturity zones. When our Peonies are done blooming yours start a month later. Same with the Lilac bushes. What maturity sweet corn do you plant up there? The picture of our garden is about a eighty five to ninety day corn.Deer fence eh.Pooch

I would have to ask my gardener about maturity to be sure, but I think she has used an 80 day Super Sweet type in the past. The wolves have about wiped out my local deer population, so about all the fence is good for now is to keep the dog out of the garden, he loves carrots.

Carrots? When we had Basset hounds years ago, it was always a race between them and Peg for the green beans. They loved green beans for some reason. Kind of like racoons and our sweet corn patch. Pooch
